The paper deals with graph properties and their testing, which falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of spectral graph theory suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper's focus on algorithmic techniques for property testing suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
